According to the practice of most
organizations,

7
00:00:38,788 --> 00:00:39,825
we find that

8
00:00:40,228 --> 00:00:42,397
there are usually

9
00:00:43,327 --> 00:00:45,644
five types of organizational structures.

10
00:00:46,210 --> 00:00:47,934
They are: functional organizational
structure

11
00:00:48,684 --> 00:00:49,768
product organizational structure,

12
00:00:50,459 --> 00:00:51,434
geographic organizational structure,

13
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:52,983
customer organizational structure and

14
00:00:53,653 --> 00:00:54,349
matrix organizational structure.

15
00:00:54,675 --> 00:00:59,303
The last one is the combination of any
two or three of these four.

16
00:00:59,712 --> 00:01:01,460
Let's look at more details about them.

17
00:01:02,595 --> 00:01:03,946
First of all,  the functional
organizational structure.

18
00:01:04,216 --> 00:01:06,405
This type of structure

19
00:01:06,456 --> 00:01:08,589
groups individuals by specific functions
performed.

20
00:01:08,788 --> 00:01:10,465
In companies which use it,

21
00:01:11,007 --> 00:01:12,743
each department has different functions,

22
00:01:13,297 --> 00:01:14,971
and all similar functions of the company

23
00:01:15,368 --> 00:01:17,149
are grouped in one department.

24
00:01:17,875 --> 00:01:19,540
For example, an industrial corporation

25
00:01:19,908 --> 00:01:21,105
can be divided into

26
00:01:21,985 --> 00:01:23,197
manufacturing department,

27
00:01:23,694 --> 00:01:25,991
the marketing department, the finance
department

28
00:01:26,462 --> 00:01:27,597
the R&D department

29
00:01:27,854 --> 00:01:29,377
the human resources department, etc.

30
00:01:30,245 --> 00:01:32,183
The division of labour is clear-cut,

31
00:01:32,551 --> 00:01:33,617
each one being charged with specific
responsibilities.

32
00:01:34,008 --> 00:01:35,327
In this figure,

33
00:01:35,327 --> 00:01:36,088
we can see that

34
00:01:36,337 --> 00:01:37,940
in the headquarters of the company,

